The paper is focused on recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of data mining and recommendation techniques also suggests a potential fit with the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation process and user-oriented challenges may also align with the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the focus on user experience and potential future directions suggest a possible fit with the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
